# ROS2

ROS2 tooling and patterns. For framework-agnostic robotics guidance (frames, control, safety), see `robotics.mdc`.

## Build and run
- Build with `colcon build`, source the overlay (`source install/setup.bash`), and launch via `ros2 launch <pkg> <file>.launch.py`.
- Keep `package.xml` dependencies accurate; declare build vs exec deps correctly.

## Topics, services, actions
- Name interfaces by purpose within a namespace (e.g. `/arm/joint_states`, `/nav/cmd_vel`). Reuse standard `*_msgs` types instead of inventing new ones.
- Use services for request/response, actions for long-running goals with feedback/cancel, topics for streaming.

## QoS
- Match QoS profiles to the data: sensor streams use best-effort/volatile; commands and latched state use reliable/transient-local. Mismatched QoS silently drops messages.

## Parameters
- Declare parameters with defaults and load them from YAML config; never hardcode tunables. Support runtime reconfiguration where it matters.

## Node design
- Prefer lifecycle nodes for managed startup/shutdown. Use callback groups and a multi-threaded executor to isolate real-time callbacks from slow work.
- Keep callbacks short and non-blocking; offload heavy work off the executor thread.

## Testing
- Use `launch_testing` + `colcon test`; verify with `colcon test-result --verbose`. Record `ros2 bag` during integration tests for telemetry inspection.
